    THE KEY STRUCTURAL DISCOVERY.  Six superficially different impossibility
    results —

        IT.5  ATOMIC-BARRIER  coNP-hard      (relation ≤ₚ,   class coNP)
        IT.7  N-EQUIV         Π⁰₂-complete   (relation ≤_m,   class Π⁰₂)
        IT.8  CE-EQ           Σ⁰₂-complete   (relation ≤_m,   class Σ⁰₂)
        IT.11 SUBPREORDER     coNP-hard      (relation ≤ₚ,   class coNP)
        IT.13 Σ*-UNIQUE       Π₁-complete    (relation ≤ₘ,   class Π₁)
        IT.14 MULTI-Y         W[1]-hard      (relation ≤_FPT, class W[1])

    — are ALL the SAME theorem instantiated over different (relation, class) pairs.
    Each carries a triple `(R, InC, Hard)` with `Hard P := ∀ Q, InC Q → R Q P`
    and a `transfer` lemma `R A B → Hard A → Hard B` proved purely from
    transitivity of `R`.  We abstract this into ONE structure `HardnessKernel`
    and prove the generic *reduction-poset* facts ONCE:

      • `genTransfer`        : a single reduction edge propagates hardness;
      • `genTransferChain`   : hardness propagates along a 2-edge chain (the
