      • `genCommonRoot`      : if a root `S` is hard and `S ≤ A`, `S ≤ B`, then BOTH
                               targets are hard — the *fan-out* shape every IT.* has;
      • `genConfluence`      : two targets reachable from one hard root, plus a
                               cross-edge `A ≤ B`, force `B` hard via TWO independent
                               routes (root→B directly, and root→A→B), which the
                               poset must identify — a genuine transitive-reduction
